cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CL, cs.SE, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with a proof system for a logic that extends first-order intuitionistic logic with fixed points and a "generic quantifier", which is used to reason about the dynamics of bindings in object systems encoded in the logic. This makes it relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including logic (cs.LO), programming languages (cs.PL), computational linguistics (cs.CL), software engineering (cs.SE), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, since the paper focuses on the technical details of the cut-elimination proof, it is most likely to be classified under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
